name: Matt Gaetz
summary: Former President Trump has nominated Florida Representative Matt Gaetz to be the next Attorney General. This nomination has been met with shock and surprise, as Gaetz has been under investigation by the Justice Department for alleged sex trafficking. Two women have testified that Gaetz paid them for sex, but Gaetz has denied these allegations. Trump has acknowledged that Gaetz may not be confirmed by the Senate, but he is pressing forward with his nomination. Gaetz has since resigned from Congress following the nomination. This move has left Republican senators baffled, as Gaetz is a controversial figure who may struggle to gain the necessary support for confirmation.

name: SpaceX
summary: Several news articles reported on the launch of SpaceX's Starship Flight 6 test mission. The launch from Starbase in southern Texas was successful initially, but the booster landing was aborted. SpaceX CEO Elon Musk was joined by former US President Donald Trump for the event, solidifying their bond. The launch concluded with the Starship performing a dramatic water landing. The sixth launch of the Starship was the latest in a series of test flights, with Trump witnessing this particular launch. SpaceX is reportedly preparing to launch a tender offer in December at $135 per share.
